  "prompt": "Will India ever get its Kohinoor diamond back?",
  "response": "The Kohinoor diamond has a complex history and is currently part of the British Crown Jewels. Discussions about its return to India have been ongoing for many years, with various Indian officials and cultural advocates calling for its repatriation. However, the UK government has maintained that the diamond was acquired legally. \n\nWhile there is a strong sentiment in India regarding the diamond's return, the likelihood of it being returned remains uncertain. International legal frameworks, diplomatic relations, and historical claims all play a role in this issue. Until there is a significant shift in political will or international agreements, the future of the Kohinoor diamond's return remains speculative.",
